description:
The Trouble with Girls is a satirical action series starring Lester Girls, who wants to be simply an "average guy" with a dead-end job, a plain wife, and no adventures more exciting than a good night's sleep. But Lester can't go for a drive without terrorists launching missiles at him, or walk into one of his many mansions without a beautiful, talented, curvaceous woman reposing half-dressed on his bed. Wealth, adventure, sexual magnetism, dashing good looks, and the savoir faire of a Hollywood action hero are what he calls "the curse of Girls."

The first four issues of volume two were published in colour by Comico.

description:
The Betty Pages, later changed to the correct spelling of "Bettie", was devoted entirely to stories, pictures, artwork, columns, collectibles, ads, and other items associated with Pin-Up Icon Bettie Page.

Two annuals were produced with reprints in 1990, and are highly sought after by collectors, along with the associated posters of the two Annuals.

First published in 1987-1988 and then reprinted in 1990, The Betty Pages was a digest sized comic/fanzine dedicated entirely to Bettie Page in terms of stories, artwork, pictures, collectibles and other related items.

It was published and edited by Greg Theakston and co-edited by Joe Anderko and the reprint publisher was Black Cat Books.

Signifcant writing and illustrating contributors included: Glenn Barr, Dave Stevens, Chris Gore and Jim Steranko amongst others.
name: The Betty Pages Digest

description:
Published by AC Comics, "Nightveil/Colt" One-Shot Flipbook is the only book in its volume.

It features 2 different covers on each side of the comic and has a photograph of a female model dressed in each respective character 's costume.

Each side of the comic also features a story written and penciled by Bill Black with each story focusing on the character featured on that side's cover. One side has Nightveil, one side has Colt.

Nightveil is the magic wielding character of the Femforce team while Colt is essentially the espionage and weapons master of Femforce.
name: Nightveil/Colt One-Shot
